ship}}\n{{Iran squad 2010 Asian Games Volleyball}}\n{{Iran squad 2011 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship}}\n{{Iran squad 2011 FIVB Men's World Cup}}\n{{Iran squad 2013 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship}}\n{{Iran squad 2013 FIVB Men's World Grand Champions Cup}}\n{{Iran squad 2014 FIVB Volleyball World League}}\n{{Iran squad 2014 FIVB Men's World Championship}}\n{{Iran squad 2014 Asian Games Volleyball}}\n{{Iran squad 2015 FIVB Men's World Cup}}\n{{Iran squad 2016 Summer Olympics Men's Volleyball}}\n{{Iran squad 2017 FIVB Men's World Grand Champions Cup}}\n{{Iran squad 2018 Asian Games Volleyball}}\n{{Iran squad 2018 FIVB Men's World Championship}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mousavi, Mohammad}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Iranian men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Iranian expatriate sportspeople in Poland]]\n[[Category:People from Dezful]]\n[[Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Iran]]\n[[Category:Asian Games silver medalists for Iran]]\n[[Category:Asian Games medalists in volleyball]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2014 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2018 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Olympic volleyball players of Iran]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2014 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Iranian volleyball player}}\n{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Mohammad Mousavi\n| image          = Mohammad Mousavi during a volleyball match between Iran and the United States.jpg\n| image_size     = 250px\n| caption        = Mousavi after a victory against [[United States men's national volleyball team|the United States national team]] \u2013 June 2015\n| fullname       = Seyed Mohammad Mousavi Eraghi\n| nationality    = {{flagicon|IRN}} [[Iran|Iranian]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1987|8|22|mf=y}}\n| birth_place    = {{flagicon|IRN}} [[Dezful]], [[Iran]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    =  \n| height         = 200 cm\n| weight         = 95 kg  \n| spike          = 362 cm\n| block          = \n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentclub    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn]]\n| currentnumber  = 66\n| years          = 2006\u20132011<br />2011\u20132012<br />2012\u20132013<br />2013\u20132014<br />2014\u20132015<br />2015\u20132018<br />2018\u20132019<br />2019\u20132020\n| clubs          = {{flagicon|IRN}} [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]<br />{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Giti Pasand Isfahan VC|Giti Pasand Isfahan]]<br />{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Kaleh Mazandaran VC|Kalleh Mazandaran]]<br />{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Matin Varamin VC|Matin Varamin]]<br />{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]<br />{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Sarmayeh Bank Tehran VC|Sarmayeh Bank Tehran]]<br />{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Shahrdari Urmia VC|Shahrdari Urmia]]<br />{{flagicon|POL}} [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn]]\n\n| nationalyears  = 2005\u20132006<br />2004\u20132007<br />2007\u2013\n| nationalteam   = {{flagicon|IRN}} [[Iran men's national volleyball team|Iran U19]]<br />{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Iran men's national volleyball team|Iran U21]]<br />{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Iran national volleyball team|Iran]]\n| medaltemplates =\n{{MedalCountry|{{IRI}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball World Grand Champions Cup|World Grand Champions Cup]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2017 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Grand Champions Cup|2017 Japan]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|Asian Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2019 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2019 Tehran]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2013 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2013 Dubai]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2011 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2011 Tehran]]|}} \n{{MedalSilver|[[2009 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2009 Manila]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Volleyball at the Asian Games|Asian Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[Volleyball at the 2018 Asian Games \u2013 Men's tournament|2018 Jakarta-Palembang]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[Volleyball at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men|2014 Incheon]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[Volleyball at the 2010 Asian Games \u2013 Men|2010 Guangzhou]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Asian Men's Volleyball Cup|Asian Cup]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2010 Asian Men's Volleyball Cup|2010 Urmia]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2008 Asian Men's Volleyball Cup|2008 Nakhon Ratchasima]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Seyed Mohammad Mousavi Eraghi''' ({{lang-fa|\u0633\u06cc\u062f \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0645\u0648\u0633\u0648\u06cc \u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642\u06cc}}, born 22 August 1987 in [[Dezful]]) is a [[volleyball]] player from [[Iran]], who plays as a middle blocker for Polish club [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn]] and the [[Iran men's national volleyball team]].<ref>{{cite web|title=POL M: Transfer bomb! Mousavi signs with Olsztyn, will play his first season abroad|url=https://www.worldofvolley.com/Latest_news/Poland/106376/pol-m-transfer-bomb-mousavi-signs-with-olsztyn-will-play-his-first-season-abroad.html|publisher=www.worldofvolley.com|accessdate=10 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Name==\nHis family is originally from [[Arak, Iran]], and because in the past the city's name was \"[[Persian Iraq|Eragh-e Ajam]]\" (meaning Persian Iraq, or non-Arab Iraq) his family name is followed by \"Eraghi\" (Iraqi).\n\n==Career==\n\n===National team===\nMousavi was invited to national team in 2008. He was named Best Blocker at the [[2008 FIVB Men's World Olympic Qualification Tournaments|2008 Olympic Qualification Tournament]], where Iran ended up on sixth place and missed qualification for the [[Volleyball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]], [[China]]. He was named twice the Best Blocker in [[Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|Asian Championship]]. He made a brilliant performance in [[2013 FIVB Volleyball World League|2013 World League]] and was named Second Best Middle Blocker in [[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2015 World Cup]].\n\n===Clubs===\nHe started his career in volleyball club Loulehsazi Ahvaz. He played for Petrochimi Bandar Imam, [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]], [[Giti Pasand Isfahan VC|Giti Pasand Isfahan]], [[Kalleh Mazandaran VC|Kalleh Mazandaran]], [[Matin Varamin VC|Matin Vatamin]]. Mousavi has won nine championships in ten years while playing for five teams in [[Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Super League]].\nHe has received offers to play for some of the world\u2019s leading teams, including Al Arabi of Qatar and an unnamed Italian [[Italian Volleyball League|Serie A]] club but decided to play in Iranian League.\nHe was named the Best Blocker in [[2010 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|2010 Club World Championship]] with Paykan.\nHe played for three years in [[Sarmayeh Bank Tehran VC|Sarmayeh Bank]] until 2018.\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2010 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Qatar 2010]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n\n* '''[[AVC Club Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian Club Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2007 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Bahrain 2007]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2008 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Kazakhstan 2008]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2009 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|United Arab Emirates 2009]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2010 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|China 2010]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2013 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Iran 2013]] \u